Create the following React components:

1. ProfilePage: Main container component
2. ProfileHeader: Contains avatar and basic user info
3. XpProgressSection: Shows level and XP progress bars
4. AchievementsSection: Grid of achievement badges
5. SurveyHistorySection: List of completed surveys
6. CommunitiesSection: Shows community memberships

Implement responsive layout using a card-based design with the existing PersonaSync aesthetic (purple/pink gradients).

Example ProfilePage component structure:
```tsx
const ProfilePage: React.FC<{ userId: string }> = ({ userId }) => {
  const [profile, setProfile] = useState<UserProfile | null>(null);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);

  useEffect(() => {
    // Fetch user profile data
    const fetchProfile = async () => {
      try {
        setLoading(true);
        const data = await getUserProfile(userId);
        setProfile(data);
      } catch (error) {
        console.error('Failed to fetch profile:', error);
      } finally {
        setLoading(false);
      }
    };

    fetchProfile();
  }, [userId]);

  if (loading) return <LoadingSpinner />;
  if (!profile) return <ErrorState message="Profile not found" />;

  return (
    <div className="profile-container">
      <ProfileHeader user={profile} />
      <div className="profile-content">
        <XpProgressSection level={profile.level} xp={profile.xp} totalXp={profile.totalXp} />
        <AchievementsSection achievements={profile.achievements} />
        <SurveyHistorySection surveys={profile.surveyHistory} />
        <CommunitiesSection communities={profile.communityMemberships} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};
```

Use shadcn/ui components for consistent styling and implement responsive design using CSS Grid and Flexbox.

Integrate with the existing avatar generation system and extend it to support more detailed character representations:

1. Create an AvatarDisplay component that can render avatars based on character descriptions
2. Support the 3D rendered style mentioned in the PRD
3. Implement styling options for avatars (hair style, clothing, etc.)

```tsx
interface AvatarProps {
  userId: string;
  avatarUrl?: string;
  description?: string;
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg' | 'xl';
  animated?: boolean;
}

const AvatarDisplay: React.FC<AvatarProps> = ({
  userId,
  avatarUrl,
  description,
  size = 'md',
  animated = false
}) => {
  // If avatarUrl is provided, use it directly
  if (avatarUrl) {
    return (
      <div className={`avatar-container size-${size}`}>
        <img 
          src={avatarUrl} 
          alt={description || `User avatar`} 
          className={`avatar-image ${animated ? 'animated' : ''}`}
        />
      </div>
    );
  }

  // Otherwise, generate avatar based on description or userId
  return (
    <div className={`avatar-container size-${size}`}>
      {/* Integrate with existing avatar generation system */}
      <GeneratedAvatar 
        userId={userId}
        description={description}
        animated={animated}
      />
    </div>
  );
};
```

